summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from Ferdinand Schmitz and Emma Schmitz, his wife, to the City of Seattle, dated the 2nd day of April, in the year of our Lord One Thousand Nine Hundred and Twenty (1912) to a tract of land lying in the East one-fourth (E 1/4) of the Northeast quarter (NE 1/4) of the Northeast Quarter (NE 1/4) of Section Fifteen (15), Township Twenty-four (24), N. R. 3 East W. M.
